messages.message:
Patch Set 1: Verified+1 Code-Review+1

This is working here for me

Patch Set 2: -Code-Review

Hmmm....This apparently only affects the m4a container....Dunno what's up with that.

Patch Set 2: Code-Review+1

OK, apparently this is a MediaStore bug we're working around that's fixed in Android 11.

Patch Set 2: -Code-Review

Ah, it appears I removed the fallback to sorting by title if track doesn't exist. I'll have to try fixing that later.

Patch Set 3: Verified+1 Code-Review+1

Tested on 17.1 for MP3 and AAC/M4A files with and without embedded metadata (metadata from iTunes and Google Play), for FLAC with embedded metadata (CD rip w/ Kodi), and for OPUS files without metadata. In all cases Eleven now sorts the files in the correct album order, while it displayed track #10 second for both MP3 and AAC files with embedded metadata.

messages.message:
Patch Set 1:

This is an alternative to 306595.

Patch Set 1:

This additionally fixes the case with playing all the songs by an artist. By default, an artist detail view will show all the songs in alphabetical order, but the overflow menu options will just play all the albums back to back, sorted by some internal album ID. This should make it match whatever you have displayed, which is whatever sorting order you select in the overall songs view (the sorting order for the songs from an artist matches the sorting order for all the songs in your library)

Verified that songs are now added to the queue in the same order as displayed, rather than always in album order.

messages.message:
Patch Set 1: Verified+1 Code-Review+1

As far as I can tell, the old code was a broken mess. It happened regularly to me that when I paused playback when the app was in background, the song queue appeared empty when I brought it back to foreground because the service reference was null.

The sKnownTokens logic still isn't ideal (ideally each piece of code talking to the service should have their own service registration), but changing that seems like a huge refactoring, so this solution looks good enough for now to me.

Patch Set 1: -Verified Code-Review-1

Need to call startService when starting playback.

Patch Set 5: Code-Review-1

Need to keep service in foreground during transient loss of focus. Working on it...

The "android.hidl.base@1.0_system" and "android.hidl.manager@1.0_system" are not the finished blobs, but just build makefile names. You can name those whatever you want tbh.

The installed module name is the actual name of the completed blob which as I mentioned before would be "android.hidl.base@1.0.so" and "android.hidl.manager@1.0.so" which I'm guessing s2 blobs do use as our blobs are probably too old.
